Let's do one more.

00:07:18.000 --> 00:07:27.000
And now we will have the bond here,

00:07:27.000 --> 00:07:52.720
one, two, three, four, like so.
And so now you see a repeat unit.

00:07:52.720 --> 00:07:58.180
Here is a repeat unit. And this
repeat unit can go n times where n

00:07:58.180 --> 00:08:03.630
is very, very large.
N can be on the order of ten

00:08:03.630 --> 00:08:09.080
thousand or so giving us molecules
that have atomic masses of a million

00:08:09.080 --> 00:08:14.540
grams per mole.
These are huge.

00:08:14.540 --> 00:08:32.080
We call this n. I am using n now
