And why is it doing this?

00:14:18.600 --> 00:14:23.000
It is doing this to maximize Van
der Waals bonding here.

00:14:23.000 --> 00:14:47.400
The tighter it packs, the greater
the intensity of bond formation.

00:14:47.400 --> 00:15:06.400
We see this happening in the
formation of such zones

00:14:31.800 --> 00:14:56.160
of crystallinity.
And when this happens we have a

00:14:56.160 --> 00:15:00.490
change in properties.
Let's consider low-density

00:15:00.490 --> 00:15:04.830
polyethylene. Well,
we know that this thing is going to

00:15:04.830 --> 00:15:09.160
