00:16:03.350 --> 00:16:07.490
There is a little bit of tighter
packing here. But what happens when

00:16:07.490 --> 00:16:11.640
we get into these zones of
regularity, because there is a

00:16:11.640 --> 00:16:15.780
higher atom density,
this turns out to have a higher

00:16:15.780 --> 00:16:19.920
reactivity with light.
Therefore, I am using n here not to

00:16:19.920 --> 00:16:24.540
mean index of polymerization.
This is index of refraction.

00:16:24.540 --> 00:16:29.630
The index of refraction in the near
crystalline zones is not equal to

00:16:29.630 --> 00:16:34.720
the index of refraction in the
amorphous zones.

00:16:34.720 --> 00:16:39.810
Now we have zones that are near
crystalline in zones that are

00:16:39.810 --> 00:16:44.900
amorphous. And so we have the
effect of internal interface.

00:16:44.900 --> 00:17:03.600
And, as a result, the high-density
polyethylene is opaque.

00:16:30.000 --> 00:16:38.300
These zones here add rigidity.

00:16:38.300 --> 00:17:04.890
There is a stiffness here. This
one is rigid. What do we have?

00:17:04.890 --> 00:17:11.490
We have low-density polyethylene.
